# Avoid Duplicates

When working in this repo, avoid creating duplicates and clean up ones you find.

## Before adding a new file

- Check if the **same or equivalent content** already exists in that course (e.g. same PDF in another week, or a " (1)" copy).
- If it does: **move or rename** the existing file instead of adding a second copy; update README/INDEX if the path changes.

## When reorganising

- Prefer **rename/move** over copy so the old location is gone. Don’t leave the same file in two places.
- After moving, remove the old path (or replace it); update any README/INDEX that referenced it.

## Clean up when you spot

| Sign of duplicate | Action |
|-------------------|--------|
| ` (1)` or `(2)` in filename (e.g. `LECTURA Judt (1).pdf`) | Rename to a clear name (e.g. `judt-origins-of-european-union.pdf`); delete the duplicate if it’s a true copy. |
| Same basename in multiple week folders | Confirm which week is correct; keep one, fix or remove the other; update docs. |
| Backup/copy leftovers (`.bak`, `-copy`, `-old`, `*backup*`) | Remove if not needed; don’t commit cruft. |
| Two files that are the same content, different names | Keep one clear name; remove or redirect the other; update README/INDEX. |

## After cleanup

Update **README** and **docs/INDEX.md** if any paths or listed filenames changed (see "Always update README and INDEX" rule).
